The paper discusses techniques for protecting intellectual property in electronic circuits, which falls under the category of hardware security. The use of spin-based devices and Boolean satisfiability attacks suggests a focus on emerging technologies (cs.ET) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The discussion of layout camouflaging and invasive monitoring at runtime suggests a focus on computer architecture (cs.AR) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the use of state-of-the-art Boolean satisfiability attacks suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) as well.
